                   "message":  "POSTMENU-AUDIT-CLEANUP: cover reset_camera CAD-projection branch + record menu-bar arc\n\nCloses the two findings from the post-menu-arc 5-axis audit. No feature code, no\nCargo, no broad docs reconcile.\n\nLAYER-1 (test gap): EditorShell::current_scene_bounds\u0027 CAD-projection arm\n(lifecycle/mod.rs ~1672-1678) was untested — reset_camera (View -\u003e Reset Camera,\nnow user-reachable) could silently fall back to the default pose on the CAD\nauthoring path with no test signal. Adds reset_camera_frames_cad_projection_scene\nto lifecycle/tests.rs: builds a non-unit (4x2x6) CAD cuboid (a 1x1x1 origin cube\nframes to the default (3,3,3) pose, which couldn\u0027t separate this arm from the\nNone-fallback), computes the expected isometric framing from the SAME\nrender_mesh_for call the branch makes, and asserts reset_camera reproduces it\n(provably distinct from default) after a camera clobber. The prebuilt + None arms\nwere already covered.\n\nLAYER-2 (doc omission): the editor-egui-host crate-root `# Dispatch arc` module\ndoc listed Dispatch A-F + EDITOR-SAVE-STATUS-INDICATOR but never recorded the\nmenu-bar arc it now hosts. Adds a MENU-BAR ARC entry (the four registry menus +\nhost-\u003eshell MenuCommandHandoff, the MenuStateHandoff Play enablement, the\nFile/Edit accelerator display, and the menu submodule extracted by\nEGUIHOST-MENU-EXTRACTION). Public intra-doc links only; the private `menu`\nmodule\u0027s items are plain code spans (no private-link warning).\n\nTest + doc-comment only; no behaviour change. The near-cap files\n(cad-projection/src/lib.rs @995, round_fillet/loft.rs @996) stay on the watchlist\n(no action). Gate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints; the 3 reset_camera tests pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
